  "prompt": "How has legislation evolved to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Legislation combating money laundering has evolved significantly over time:\n\n1. Early Stages\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) in US\n- Initial focus on reporting large cash transactions\n- Limited international cooperation\n\n2. Key Milestones\n- FATF establishment (1989)\n- International standards and recommendations\n- Increased global coordination\n- Enhanced reporting requirements\n\n3. Major Legislative Developments\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (2020)\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- Stricter penalties\n- Broader regulatory scope\n\n4. Technology-Driven Changes\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Cryptocurrency regulation\n- Advanced tracking mechanisms\n- Real-time suspicious activity detection\n\n5. Expanded Scope\n- Covering more financial institutions\n- Including non-banking sectors\n- Addressing emerging financial technologies\n- Targeting terrorist financing\n\n6. International Collaboration\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing protocols\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n- Cross-border investigation mechanisms\n\n7. Recent Trends\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Enhanced beneficial ownership transparency\n- Machine learning/AI in detection\n- More comprehensive risk assessment frameworks\n\nThese evolutionary stages demonstrate increasing complexity and sophistication in money laundering prevention strategies.",
